feed.title: Post Politics: Breaking Politics News, Political Analysis & More - The Washington Post
feed.description: Post Politics from The Washington Post is the source for political news headlines, in-depth politics coverage and political opinion, plus breaking news on the Obama administration and White House, Congress, the Supreme Court, elections and more.

entries.title: The Fix: This is what a non-candidate Elizabeth Warren looks like for 2016
entries.contentSnippet: Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D-Mass.) has been everywhere these past few days. CNN! CBS! Conan! The Daily Show! She was out promoting ...
entries.content: Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D-Mass.) has been everywhere these past few days. CNN! CBS! Conan! The Daily Show! She was out promoting the paperback edition of her book "A Fighting Chance," but her timing also coincided with the final days before Hillary Clinton officially announces she's running for president (Sunday).Read full article >>

entries.title: O’Malley, Webb appear before Iowa Democrats as Clinton waits in the wings
entries.contentSnippet: DES MOINES, Iowa — Two of Hillary Rodham Clinton’s potential Democratic rivals made pitches to a party gathering here Friday ...
entries.content: DES MOINES, Iowa — Two of Hillary Rodham Clinton’s potential Democratic rivals made pitches to a party gathering here Friday night, with both telling activists that more needs to be done to protect the American Dream.Read full article >>

entries.title: Obama criticizes foes of Iran nuclear outline, says Congress has limited role
entries.contentSnippet: PANAMA CITY — President Obama said Saturday that he looks forward to engaging Congress in the coming week, not on the specifics ...
entries.content: PANAMA CITY — President Obama said Saturday that he looks forward to engaging Congress in the coming week, not on the specifics of the framework agreement over Iran’s nuclear program, but on the “narrow question” of “what’s Congress’s appropriate role in looking at a final deal” to be negotiated by the end of June.Read full article >>

entries.title: Obama’s meeting with Castro infuriates GOP presidential candidates
entries.contentSnippet: President Obama’s face-to-face meeting with Cuban President Raul Castro on Saturday angered Republican candidates vying to ...
entries.content: President Obama’s face-to-face meeting with Cuban President Raul Castro on Saturday angered Republican candidates vying to succeed him — and might help elevate an issue that so far hasn’t resonated widely among GOP primary voters. Read full article >>

entries.title: NEA: No Child Left Behind rewrite doesn’t level the playing field
entries.contentSnippet: The head of the country’s largest teachers union said that her organization does not support a bipartisan proposal in the ...
entries.content: The head of the country’s largest teachers union said that her organization does not support a bipartisan proposal in the Senate to replace the nation’s main federal education law because it does not go far enough to create equal educational opportunities for poor children.Read full article >>

entries.title: Ready For Hillary holds one last event in New York, its mission accomplished
entries.contentSnippet: It's a coincidence that what will most likely be the last rally held by Ready For Hillary took place at a crowded bar in Lower ...
entries.content: It's a coincidence that what will most likely be the last rally held by Ready For Hillary took place at a crowded bar in Lower Manhattan on Saturday. Planned several months ago, according to event co-chair Ny Whitaker, it just happened to end up marking what will almost certainly be the last day of the Democratic 2016 preseason, fewer than 24 hours before the group's stated dream comes true: Hillary Clinton announces her candidacy for the presidency.Read full article >>

entries.title: Paul: ‘I’m unafraid to challenge the status quo’
entries.contentSnippet: LAS VEGAS — Rand Paul had done some counting, and he didn't like the way the numbers were adding up."I found out that the ...
entries.content: LAS VEGAS — Rand Paul had done some counting, and he didn't like the way the numbers were adding up."I found out that the Lord's Prayer is 66 words long. The Gettysburg Address is 286 words long. The Declaration of Independence is 1,322 words long," Paul said to an overflowing crowd at a community center here. "But the government regulation for the sale of cabbage is 26,911 words long."Read full article >>

entries.title: Iowa Democrats want Hillary Clinton to woo them
entries.contentSnippet: DES MOINES — She’s an icon known across the world by just her first name, but when Hillary Rodham Clinton touches down here in ...
entries.content: DES MOINES — She’s an icon known across the world by just her first name, but when Hillary Rodham Clinton touches down here in Iowa this week to kick off her second presidential campaign, she will be greeted by enormous expectations of intimacy.Read full article >>

entries.title: Clinton campaign issues mission statement: ‘We Are Hillary For America’
entries.contentSnippet: On the eve of her presidential campaign launch, Hillary Rodham Clinton's campaign-in-waiting issued a mission statement ...
entries.content: On the eve of her presidential campaign launch, Hillary Rodham Clinton's campaign-in-waiting issued a mission statement Saturday describing its purpose as giving "every family, every small business and every American a path to lasting prosperity."Read full article >>

entries.title: For Republicans, ‘Stop Hillary’ campaign begins in earnest
entries.contentSnippet: The deluge of derision this weekend from Republicans responding to Hillary Rodham Clinton’s presidential launch is the start of ...
entries.content: The deluge of derision this weekend from Republicans responding to Hillary Rodham Clinton’s presidential launch is the start of a highly coordinated effort by national GOP leaders and conservative groups to effectively begin the general-election campaign against the likely Democratic nominee.Read full article >>
